Telkom Kenya First-Half Sales Fall on Call Rates, Standard Says

-- B y   P a u l   R i c h a r d s o n
-- 
2011-08-01T04:37:41Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-01/telkom-kenya-first-half-revenue-drops-on-lower-call-rates-standard-says.html
Telkom  Kenya  Ltd. posted a 21 percent
decline in first-half sales as average revenue per user dropped
after call rates were cut, the Standard reported, citing parent
company  France Telecom SA. (FTE)   Revenue declined to 38 million euros ($54.7 million) in the
six months through June from 48 million a year earlier, the
Nairobi-based newspaper said today.  Telkom Kenya grew its market share to 8.5 percent by the
end of December and the company now has about 2.5 million
customers, the newspaper said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
 Paul Richardson  at 
 pmrichardson@bloomberg.net  